The team&rsquo;s approach, which used <ins>large doses of the flu drug oseltamivir combined with HIV drugs lopinavir and ritonavir</ins>, improved the conditions of several patients at the Rajavithi Hospital in Bangkok.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;This is not the cure, but the patient&rsquo;s condition has vastly improved,&rdquo; Rajavithi Hospital&rsquo;s Kriangsak Atipornwanich says of one 70-year-old Chinese woman from Wuhan, according to Reuters. &ldquo;From testing positive for 10 days under our care, after applying this combination of medicine the test result became negative within 48 hours.&rdquo;

